revision.text:
An '''aquamog''' is a machine for removing weeds growing over a body of water. An aquamog was used in 2018 for removing [[water primrose]] from North Lake in San Francisco's [[Golden Gate Park]]. A newspaper photo shows a machine similar to a [[backhoe]] on very wide [[Continuous track|crawlers]].<ref>{{cite news |title='Aquamog' to the rescue! Weed eater takes on invasive species in Golden Gate Park |author=Christien Kafton |date=November 5, 2018 |publisher=[[Fox News]] |url=http://www.ktvu.com/news/-aquamog-to-the-rescue-weed-eater-takes-on-invasive-species-in-golden-gate-park#/ |accessdate=November 22, 2018}}</ref>
The name ''aquamog'' was derived from the multi-purpose vehicle ''[[Unimog]]'' produced by [[Mercedes Benz]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Aquamogs |url=http://aquamog.net/aquamogs/aquamogs/ |accessdate=November 22, 2018}}</ref>
