'''Brand Affinity Technologies''' ('''BAT''') is a [[technology]] and [[marketing]] services company.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Elliott|first1=Stuart|title=A Place Where Sponsors Sign Athletes|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2009/10/19/business/media/19adcol.html|accessdate=26 September 2017|publisher=The New York Times|date=18 October 2009}}</ref> It was founded by brother entrepreneurs [[Ryan Steelberg]] and [[Chad Steelberg]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Ali|first1=Rafat|title=The dMarc Brothers: Where Are They Now?|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2008/09/02/AR2008090202539.html|accessdate=26 September 2017|publisher=The Washington Post|date=2 September 2008}}</ref> In October 2012, Brand Affinity Technologies acquired Printroom, a leading [[fan (person)|fan]] [[photography]] business.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ocregister.com/2012/10/28/marketing-firm-buys-fan-photo-website/|title=Marketing firm buys fan photo website|date=28 October 2012|publisher=}}</ref>
