The '''M1 MSBS''' was the first French [[submarine-launched ballistic missile]]. In French, MSBS is the abbreviation for ''Mer-Sol Balistique Stratégique'', or Sea-Ground Strategic Ballistic Missile. It has two [[Multistage rocket|stages]]. It was deployed on the [[Redoutable-class submarine (1967)|''Redoutable''-class]] SNLEs (''Sous-marin Nucléaire Lanceur d'Engins'') (Device-launching Nuclear Submarine) or [[SSBN]]s from 1971 to 1975. It was replaced by the [[M2 (missile)|M2 MSBS]] in 1974-75.<ref>[http://www.astronautix.com/lvs/msbsm1.htm MSBS M1 at Astronautix.com]</ref>

