{{For|other buildings called the 511 Building|511 Building (disambiguation)}} {{Infobox building | name = Minnesota Technology Center | former_names = | alternate_names = | image = 511 Building (Minneapolis).JPG | caption = | map_type = | altitude = | building_type = | architectural_style = | structural_system = | cost = | ren_cost = | location = [[Minneapolis, Minnesota|Minneapolis]], [[Minnesota]] | address = 511 11th Avenue South | client = | owner = | current_tenants = | landlord = TimeShare Systems, Inc. | coordinates = {{Coord|44|58|18.3|N|93|15|17|W|type:landmark_region:US-MN |display=inline,title}} | start_date = | completion_date = | inauguration_date = 1982 | renovation_date = 2003 | demolition_date = | destruction_date = | height = | diameter = | other_dimensions = | floor_count = 3 | floor_area = 273,000 sq ft | main_contractor = | architect = | architecture_firm = | structural_engineer = | services_engineer = | civil_engineer = | other_designers = | quantity_surveyor = | awards = | ren_architect = | ren_firm = | ren_str_engineer = | ren_serv_engineer = | ren_civ_engineer = Palanisami & Associates, Inc. | ren_oth_designers = | ren_qty_surveyor = | ren_awards = | references = <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.officespace.com/osoweb/bldghistory.cfm?BuildingID=-92454493|title=OfficeSpace.com - Minnesota Technology Center History|publisher=}}</ref> }}
The '''Minnesota Technology Center''', formerly called the '''BTC/Bunker''' and also known as the '''511 Building''' in reference to its address, is a [[colocation centre|colocation center]] located in downtown [[Minneapolis, Minnesota]], near [[U.S. Bank Stadium]] and the West Bank campus of the [[University of Minnesota]]. The 511 Building has been referred to as "the most wired building in Minnesota" and is a major source of fiber optic data transmission and reception.<ref name="strib">{{Cite news |url=http://www.startribune.com/local/south/112686079.html |title=Eagan eager to boot up data center |last=Marquez Estrada |first=Heron |date=2010-12-31 |newspaper=[[Star Tribune]]}}</ref> It is operated by Timeshare Systems Inc. It hosts an interchange between many major carriers, and is on the [[Internet Backbone]].<ref>[http://web.mac.com/kharbanda/iweb/511/511%20Flyer.html 511 building flyer]{{dead link|date=December 2016}}</ref>
The City of Minneapolis budgeted almost $750,000 to rent space at the center for a security command center during the [[2018 Super Bowl]] and 2019 Final Four.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://tonywebster.com/2017/05/fahrenheit-511-11th-avenue-south/ |title=Fahrenheit 511: Minneapolis Police’s Super Bowl Command Center |last=Webster |first=Tony |date=2017}}</ref>
